content:
If the CRM Analytics dashboard contains selection-based widgets (chart, date, list, range, or toggle), you can set initial selections that are applied when the dashboard first opens. For example, you can select a bar in a bar chart and set that as the initial selection.

While viewing the dashboard, a user can change the selection in the chart to filter the results differently or remove the selection and filters altogether. If a widget’s query is configured to require a selection, set the initial selection. If you don’t, CRM Analytics selects the first value when the dashboard opens.

CRM Analytics selects the value if it’s present in the results, otherwise, it attempts to search the data for the result by name. If the value is still not found, it’s unselected. You can view the initial selections in the query properties.

To set initial selections:

While editing the dashboard, click  and then select Pick Initial Selections.
CRM Analytics previews the dashboard.
Make selections in chart, date, list, range, or toggle widgets.
You can also select a row in a compare table.
Click Done.
CRM Analytics saves the selections as start values for the widget queries.

Dynamically Set Initial Selections Based on the Dashboard Viewer
You can set initial filter selections to show information that’s relevant to the logged in user. For example, you can filter a sales dashboard such that each sales rep views only their sales opportunities and performance. You can set initial filter selections based on the user ID, user name, role ID, or role name of the logged in user.

Add Selection-Based Filter Widgets to Enable Users to Filter the Results

title: Setting Initial Selections in CRM Analytics Dashboards
